- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper presents an algorithm for computing edit distance between two strings. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also likely as the paper discusses the time complexity of the algorithm. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper mentions embedding edit distance into l_1, which is a topic in information theory. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is relevant as edit distance can be viewed as a geometric problem. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with combinatorial objects (strings) and their distances.
